title OAuth2 client perspective flow

Client->Gluu: A client register spontaneous \n scopes templates as regular expression: `^transaction:.+$`
Client->Gluu: Later the client request an access token with the scope \n which matches regexp above: `transaction:123asd`
Gluu->Client: Gluu Server matches the scope to the template and persists the scope\n with some configured TTL, issue the access token to the client: `transaction:123asd` 
note over Client
Now client can use the access token to 
transaction-related requests to API.
end note
